CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1958, pg. 2, reads: "Does This Condition Exist in Other Neighborhoods? Liquor Control Board Should Exercise Better Judgment - One of the overlooked evils in some neighborhoods of Allegheny County is the location of taverns in close proximity to churches, schools and playgrounds. Although such establishments do not operate on Sundays, their presence and the conduct of some patrons prove annoying during the week....  Central Baptist Church...near one of the three taverns in next block to church on Wylie Ave."
TitMainTitle: Fort Pitt Linen Supply Company truck parked in front of Sam's Cafe, with Central Baptist Church in background, Wylie Avenue, Hill District
